&=  \frac{1}{\sqrt{7}} \\\\
&= 0.38
\\end{aligned}
$$

We can now calculate the confidence interval using the equation:

$$
\\begin{aligned}
z_r^- &= z_r - (1.96 \times SE_{z_r}) \\\\
&= -0.56-(1.96 \times 0.38) \\\\
&= -1.30 \\\\
z_r^+ &= z_r+(1.96 \times SE_{z_r}) \\\\
&= -0.56 + (1.96 \times 0.38) \\\\
&= 0.19
\\end{aligned}
$$

We can now convert the values from *z* back to *r* using this equation:

$$
r = \frac{e^{2z_r}-1}{e^{2z_r}+1}
$$

Which gives

